On 5 July 1968 The Doors took to the stage of the Hollywood Bowl for a
legendary concert. Performing on the back of their 3rd album
"Waiting For The Sun", and the US No.1 single "Hello, I Love You",
they had been developing their live performances over the previous 2
years, and were in peak form. Now the original film footage has been
digitally scanned and restored, including 2 previously cut tracks, and
the sound has been remixed and mastered from the original multitrack
tapes by The Doors' engineer & co-producer Bruce Botnick. This is now
the definitive edition of this famous performance.
